    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - DESCRIPTION - ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS</title>
        <figure id="f1603804" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603804.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 5. Electric Windshield Wipers</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WIPER ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ELECTRIC WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>3. WIPER LINKAGE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>The windshield wiper system consists of a single, unitized, 12V electric wiper motor that operates the
            wiper arms through wiper linkage. The motor has two speeds (low and high) and a park position, which is
            controlled by a three-position switch.
        </para>
        <para>Since the electric wiper motor is of unitized construction, there is no need for motor rebuild or
            adjustments. There are no serviceable parts; the complete assembly is replaced.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
